The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Hanumant Singh still critical

OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT

 Hanumant Singh

Calcutta: Hanumant Chotu Singh, a centurion on Test debut, remains in critical condition. 

The 67-year-old, who was admitted to Mumbais Breach Candy Hospital on Monday, is still in the ICU. 

Hes on dialysis and theres fluid in his lungs His liver isnt functioning at all Were praying. The next 24 hours, we reckon, are going to be critical, a relative told The Telegraph on Friday night. 

Hailing from the royal family of Banswara, Hanumant has served cricket in different capacities: Selection committee chairman, coach (at home and overseas), manager and an ICC Match Referee. 

An accomplished strokemaker in his playing days, hes now battling it out on a dicey wicket. 




